result.execSummary:
The defendant Ann M. Dittmann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Issue of Worthless Checks(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.24(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Restitution in the amount of $146.28 paid directly to the Clerk of Court's Office prior to sentencing.  The 10% surcharge in the amount of $14.63 still due and owing - same repayment conditions apply as noted below for the Costs.

Excess restitution payment in the amount of $83.72 has been applied. Remaining costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

records.addlTxt: Restitution to Stone Ridge Piggly Wiggly - Ck No 010579

Case called @ 1:30 p.m. Defendant Ann M. Dittmann in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant does not wish to have an attorney and wishes to enter a plea. Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.   Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Ct 1 - Guilty.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Cts 2 & 3 - DRI. No statement by DE. Court orders: Rest in the amount of $146.28, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. Appeal rights given.
